Description:
Designed to impress
PRIVATE INSPECTIONS ONLY - PLEASE CONTACT US TO ARRANGE
In one of Coburg's best pockets lies this spacious newly built townhouse with a floor plan designed to impress. This home provides a fresh, functional and naturally lit open plan layout lending itself entirely to a comfortable and modern lifestyle.
Walking through the doors you are greeted by the formal living area with carpet underfoot. Leading through to a generous open plan dining/living and kitchen. The Kitchen features 40mm Caesar stone benchtops, soft closing 2pac cabinetry, double sink, 900mm stainless steel appliances and a walk-in pantry with plenty of storage space. Beyond the beautiful sheer curtains is the five panel bi-fold doors which takes your out to your own private courtyard with access to the double garage which can also be used as an undercover entertainment area for the family BBQ. Downstairs also includes a powder room.
Making your way upstairs you are greeted with a third living area and will also find three generously sized bedrooms. The enormous master bedroom features a walk-in wardrobe and an ensuite with floor to ceiling tiles, matte black fixtures and a stand-alone bathtub. The other two bedrooms include mirrored sliding built in wardrobes and serviced by a modern central bathroom.
Complementing this brand-new home is reverse cycle ducted heating and cooling, remote alarm system, LED downlights throughout and ROW access.
Perfectly positioned, within walking distance to public transport, local schools, Upfield Bike path, the vibrant Sydney, Moreland and Melville Road with its cafes and restaurants on offer, ensuring that nothing is ever out of reach!
THIS AUCTION IS AN ONLINE AUCTION:
Given the safety measures around COVID-19, we are taking our auctions completely online. You can now Watch, Bid and Buy online at this auction via the Anywhere Auctions website or app.
To Register to Bid: Please visit the Anywhere Auctions website or download the app and click on the "Register to Bid" button against this property. Registration takes five minutes and you will be able to bid online from the safety of your own home.
To View this auction: Please visit the Anywhere Auctions website or download the app and click on the "View Live Auction" button against this property.
To find out more about the bidder registration process or bidding online through the Anywhere Auctions platform for this auction, please visit the "How to bid" section of the Anywhere Auctions website.
Please contact us to find out more about our online auctions.

Description:
Space and Style with Spectacular Views!
A brilliant entry into Cosmopolitan Coburg or blue-chip investment opportunity, this fourth-floor abode is perfect either way with its intelligent design, first-class features and an uninterrupted panoramic outlook. Flanked by floor-to-ceiling windows for an abundance of natural light, the apartment's impressive interior comprises two generous bedrooms (both with mirrored robes) together with a stylish master ensuite and equally-deluxe main bathroom - both with quality fittings and floor-to-ceiling tiles. Add to this a spacious and versatile open-plan living/dining area accompanied by a superb stone-bench kitchen complete with soft-close cabinetry, mirrored splashbacks, Miele cooking appliances and Fisher & Paykel dishwasher. Along with a large undercover balcony with views over Coburg Lake all the way to the Yarra Ranges, the home also includes split-system heating and cooling, square-set ceilings and engineered timber floors, efficient LED lighting and discreet laundry facilities, plus lift to secure entry foyer and undercover parking space. Moments from the open spaces of Coburg Lake Reserve, it's also walking distance to Brosnan Community Park and endless Merri Creek trails, childcare centre, swimming pool, Coburg High School as well as easy access to Sydney Road trams, cafes, Coburg Station and renowned shopping precinct.

Contemporary Quality in Coburg's Finest
Brand new with excellence and precision, this architect designed four/five bedroom or 2nd living , four bathroom masterpiece is for families wanting modern upgrades and a fantastic locale. Description:
"Huntly" - Californian Dreaming Of The Future
Please register your interest to participate in a Brad Teal auction. Registrations allow us to maintain compliance with the latest government directions. All auctions will be held onsite and online. Contact us to find out more.
With strong street presence and potential to really shine through thoughtful renovations (subject to relevant approvals), this elevated three bedroom Californian Bungalow awaits its dream buyer. Presenting a living, kitchen/meals and private rear garden, it's immediately liveable and could make an aspirational home once more with a little inspiration: work with existing high ceilings with decorative detail, polished floorboards and a bay window to bring out its best once more. The living room comes with modern heating/air conditioning, there's a gas stove in the kitchen/meals for tasty dinners from day one and bedrooms share a conveniently central bathroom. A long side driveway leads to a garage and the position sees you close to a range of amenities and features including transport, parks, Coburg Market, Sydney Road and schools, rounding out an excellent opportunity to create the lifestyle you want in a position that can offer it all. A little less than 10 kilometres from the CBD this is where you want to be.

Key To Dynamic Living.
High end appointments fill this bright and brand new two bedroom townhouse, situated moments to tempting cafes, popular Coburg Market, lively Sydney Road and a range of transport options. From lustrous polished floorboards to sweeping stone surfaces, the ground level is a stylish vision of open plan relaxation. A range of Bosch appliances and great storage further distinguish the kitchen, there's plentiful living and dining space and a sliding glass door leads to a private northerly courtyard with both covered and open space. Sun-filled double bedrooms above host mirrored built-in robes and share a luxe fully tiled bathroom with rainfall shower and deep freestanding bath. A laundry/second toilet, heating/cooling and automatic garage add even more appeal to this glamorous home.

Create the Dream in a Sought-After Pocket
Holding a prized position on a tree lined street that is located for lifestyle, this solid brick Californian Bungalow on a 351m2 allotment (approx.) presents a brilliant opportunity to enjoy today, before commencing on your city fringe dream!
Behind a tuck-pointed façade, Baltic pine floors, ornate cornice, decorative ceiling roses adorning high ceilings, lead light detail, picture rails and open fireplaces enhance a deceptively spacious and flexible interior.
Off the central hallway, three generous bedrooms are partnered by a study, which could work just as well as fourth bedroom if desired, or even a child's playroom.
The spacious living room seamlessly transitions into an even larger living meals. It is anchored by a custom-built kitchen that features a blend of stainless steel and timber bench tops over abundant storage, a 900 mm range, and a very hand built in table perfect for meals on the go, homework and for the chef to a part of the conversation at dinner parties.
French doors draw you put to a peaceful and private rear yard which introduces extensive paving, a covered entertainment area, wood fire BBQ, established gardens, storeroom and a carport behind a roller door and accessed from a rear laneway.
Zoned to Coburg Senior High and central to Coburg Shopping Village, the train station, and the tram, shops, cafes and restaurants along cosmopolitan Sydney Road, astute buyers can look to make the most of the position, proportions and potential enjoy to create a richly rewarding future in their own time frame (stca) own time frame with this wonderfully appealing prospect.

Description:
Brand New Boutique Living in a Vibrant City Location - Only One Left!
Fantastic opportunity to experience a cosmopolitan, city edge lifestyle like no other with this brand new apartment comprising one bedroom plus study. In a boutique block of only four, the apartment enjoys stylish open plan living spaces and private balcony where large stacker doors open wide to bring the outside in. Modern floors, stone top benches, vanities, stainless steel electric appliances and oversized shower complement the kitchen and bathroom. BIRS, split-system air conditioner, European laundry, secure intercom entry and designated storage cage adds extra appeal. Opposite Lincoln Mills Homemaker Centre, cafes, health club and Bunnings, and walking distance from Coburg North Village shops, Coburg Lake, Batman station, trams and buses.
Jellis Craig Coronavirus Update
If you do arrange a private inspection we ask that you support us on the following;
- A reminder to maintain healthy social distancing (at least 1.5m) from Jellis Craig sales teams
- Keeping attendees at the appointment to a minimum
- Please refrain from touching surfaces within the property where possible
We also request you refrain from attending an inspection appointment if you have:
- Tested positive to, or have symptoms associated with Coronavirus
- Recently been in contact with someone diagnosed with Coronavirus
- Recently been overseas or agreed to any self-isolation conditions
If you are unable to attend the property but are still interested, please contact the agent and they will advise you of the best way to proceed.
We thank you for your understanding as we navigate through this period together.

Description:
Very large family home with a beautiful northern aspect
***This property is available for inspection by appointment - Please contact us to arrange a suitable time***
Nestled in a neighbourly tree-lined street, close to Coburg Lake, this superb family home has been recently refreshed across its luxuriously spacious double storey design. It presents a sought-after modern lifestyle, strolling distance to Sydney Road cafes, Merri Creek Trail, city trains and parklands, and moments to Coburg Farmer's Market and a selection of schools. Beyond the wide foyer is a light filled living and dining area, large family and casual dining area at the back, and stylish stone kitchen with stainless steel gas appliances and a breakfast bar. Step outdoors to the sun soaked entertaining deck, landscaped child-friendly garden and private courtyard. Also downstairs is a good sized laundry, powder room and automatic double garage with internal access. The first floor boasts a huge master bedroom with a walk-in robe and sparkling ensuite with a spa bath and shower, three additional generous bedrooms with built-ins and a bright stone bathroom with a bath, shower and separate w/c. Nearby is a study area and covered balcony. It features ducted heating/cooling, polished floorboards, new carpet, understair storage, downlighting and elegant neutral tones.
*** COVID-19 Announcement ***
If you're attending a Private Appointment, we request that you only attend if you are fit and healthy to do so and not under any self-isolation conditions. We request that you maintain a healthy distance from our team members, and if requested wait outside until the property is ready for the appointment. Lastly, please refrain from touching items/fixtures and doors within the properties. If you would like to view something in particular, please request the agent's assistance. Thank you.

Description:
Parkland Setting, Urban Living
* Register to attend an open for inspection*
In order to maintain a maximum of 10 attendees to all Open Inspections, we ask that you please register to attend. By registering your details, you avoid disappointment if more than 10 people attend the inspection and will assist us in keeping the inspections as safe as possible for our team and our clients.
One of the many lifestyle benefits presented by this spacious single bedroom ground floor apartment, part of the coveted Merriview Place complex, is its location. Conveniently located, it is a short distance from the many things Coburg has to offer including Sydney Roads shopping and culinary precincts. It is close to parks, a wide range of sporting reserves, bike trails and gardens, whilst only being 10 km from the Melbourne CBD, in close proximity to Northland Shopping Centre and centrally situated between the University of Melbourne and La Trobe University.
This immaculate property sits opposite Merri Creek parklands, is a stones throw from the bustle of Sydney Road, conveniently situated within a kilometre of public transport (including Coburg Station) and is a short stroll from the local Farmers Markets, Coburg Leisure Centre and parkland. Its tranquil setting belies the vibrant lifestyle on offer.
Well-presented, this sundrenched apartment with Merri Creek views as a backdrop, features an open plan living domain, stylish well-ordered kitchen with quality appliances and large bright courtyard. Add to this a communal pool and BBQ facilities making options for entertaining both inside and out easy, while a spacious bedroom with ensuite and walk-in robe, separate laundry, powder room, secure entry, lift access, secure undercover parking and store locker on title, make this, one not to miss.
Perfect for first home buyers or investors alike an inspection of this property will certainly impress.

Description:
SOLD $755,000 BY JON CHALLANDS
Executor's Auction
We are pleased to offer to the market this much loved family home in the heart of Coburg with endless potential and charm.
The home consists of 3 bedrooms (master is positioned at the front of the home with BIR), 1 bathroom, central kitchen/meals with updated appliances, formal dining and a generous size lounge room with split system, gas heater, plus central heating and stunning high ceilings throughout.
The covered outdoor alfresco entertaining area is perfect for gatherings and Sunday BBQs and the outdoor bungalow offers versatility that can be converted to a 4th bedroom, 2nd living space, home office or man cave - the possibilities are really that endless.
The block comprises 541sqm (approx.) of land with a well established front garden, side access to the rear of the property where all the hard work has been done with garden beds in place ready to be filled with your choice of flowers, plants, fruits or vegetables.
Perfectly situated in such a sought after location just moments to the buzz of Sydney Road with its cafes, bars, restaurants and nightlife and less than 10km from Melbourne's CBD.
This is your opportunity to purchase a piece of Coburg that has not been offered to the market for quite some time.
All enquiries welcomed and all inspections are by appointment only.
Land Size: 541sqm
House Size: 15sq approx
Chattels: All fixtures and fittings as inspected
Deposit: 10% of the purchase price
Rental Appraisal: $450-$500pw (approx)
Nearest Primary School: Coburg West Primary, Coburg North Primary
Nearest Secondary School: Coburg High School, Strathmore Secondary College
Nearest Public Transport: Upfield train station, Coburg train station, Bus 526/530, Tram 19
Internal area
139.35m²

Description:
A quiet oasis, minutes from Sydney Road
***this property is available for inspection by appointment-Please contact us to arrange a suitable time****
This beautifully presented single fronted brick home, with surprisingly spacious proportions, is very well located in a peaceful family neighbourhood and only minutes from Sydney Road. The house offers three large bright bedrooms: 2 with built in robes and black out blinds and one with built in book shelves. The spacious master bedroom contains a purpose built study nook and reverse cycle a/c. A sparkling central bathroom with a shower and bath join a separate laundry. The entrance hall and central hallway lead to a huge sun filled open plan kitchen, containing stainless steal appliances with Miele dishwasher. This adjoins a family and dining area which overlooks a beautifully lush private and tranquil courtyard with vertical gardens. Other features include expansive rear windows, NBN internet, attractive timber floors and carpeted bedrooms, and two reverse cycle a/c units. A short walk to fabulous Sydney Road attractions, schools & CBD transport.
No Owners Corporation Fees
*** COVID-19 Announcement ***
If you're attending an open for inspection, we request that you only attend if you are fit and healthy to do so and not under any self-isolation conditions. We request that you maintain a healthy distance from anyone attending the open for inspection, including other prospective buyers and our team members, and if requested wait outside so as to reduce the number of people in the property at any one time. Lastly, please refrain from touching items/fixtures and doors within the properties. If you would like to view something in particular, please request the agent's assistance. Thank you.

Description:
Veiled Victorian with Perfect Potential!
Please register your interest in attending the open for inspection so that we can ensure compliance with the latest regulations.
Providing a family environment of immediate function and exceptional inner-urban ease, this double-front period home provides all the necessary ingredients for an inspired renovation and significant extension (STCA). Occupying a substantial block of land, the home itself currently comprises a wide hallway accessing three genuinely large bedrooms, along with a central bathroom, neat kitchen, family/dining area and adjoining lounge. Sep outside to discover an expansive backyard with an external laundry, workshop/storeroom and plenty of room for future expansion and potential for off-street parking. A short stroll to Moreland Station and choice of tram lines, it's also close to local schools, parks and playgrounds, as well as Sydney Road's endless array of boutique shops, cool cafes and renowned restaurants.
*** COVID-19 Announcement ***
If you're attending an open for inspection, we request that you only attend if you are fit and healthy to do so and not under any self-isolation conditions. We request that you maintain a healthy distance from anyone attending the open for inspection, including other prospective buyers and our team members, and if requested wait outside so as to reduce the number of people in the property at any one time. Lastly, please refrain from touching items/fixtures and doors within the properties. If you would like to view something in particular, please request the agent's assistance. Thank you.

Description:
UNDER OFFER
Californian Excellence and Lifestyle!
Delivering an exceptional inner-urban lifestyle with its spacious floorplan, impressive enhancements and prime position in a thriving Coburg neighbourhood, this updated home presents light-filled living space, entertaining opportunities and family liveability.
Comprising a wide central hallway accessing four large bedrooms and a study/fifth bedroom, plus fully renovated bathroom with floor to ceiling tiles, and open family/dining area adjoining a spacious kitchen with stainless steel appliances.
Step outside to discover a delightfully deep backyard with a spacious decked alfresco area making it perfect for gatherings and entertainment all year round.
The location is perfect and only walking distance to a choice of tram lines, Moreland and Coburg train stations, Sydney Road's endless cafes and restaurants, as well as shops and supermarkets, popular schools, parks and Merri Creek trails.
Enquire today and don't miss out!

Not One But Three - Extended Possibilities
Raphael Houston is proud to present ......
EXPRESSIONS OF INTEREST CLOSES TUESDAY 12/05/20 AT 5:00PM
** PRIVATE INSPECTIONS ARE WELCOMED- CONTACT AGENT**
PERFECT FOR LARGE FAMILIES OR SAVVY INVESTORS. HUGE YIELD, 3 POTENTIAL RENT INCOMES
Presenting a three bedroom, two bathroom home and not 1 BUT 2 fully self-contained one bedroom units, this exciting offering is great for extended families and those seeking a bonus residence to rent out. Elevated and adorned with decorative ceiling detail, the main home presents a living room, kitchen/meals and three large bedrooms with built-in robes. Features include polished floorboards, high ceilings, headlight, heating/cooling and OSP beyond a front gate. A covered outdoor entertaining area invites relaxed barbecues, and the separate unit is quite modern with great dimensions and its own heating/cooling. Tightly held by one family for almost three decades, and situated in a superbly convenient position, these homes are ideally close to trams, trains, parks, schools, cosmopolitan Sydney Road and Coburg Market.
CONTACT Sales Executive Raphael Houston TODAY on 0404 890 888

Description:
Low Maintenance, Single-Level Living!
Situated in a neighbourly, tree-lined street, enjoy low maintenance living with this 3 bedroom, 2 living areas, 2 car space home!
Surprisingly spacious floor plan includes: 2 good-sized bedrooms with robes + 3rd bedroom or study. Perfect for a family there are 2, separate living areas. Bathroom with bath, sep WC, sep laundry. Open plan kitchen/living with island bench, gas cook top & provision for dishwasher. Sliding doors lead seamlessly to large, flat backyard, ready for a bbq!
Extra features include: single car, lock up garage + 1 x OSP and ducted heating.
Ideal location approx 1km to Coburg station, Coburg North Primary & iconic O'Heas Bakery. Easy access to major arterial & just over 9km to CBD.
Plan your life here!
